casebody.data:
MILLER v. WARDEN OF MARYLAND HOUSE OF CORRECTION [App. No. 33,

September Term, 1963.]

Decided May 7, 1964.

Before Bruñe, C. J., and Henderson, Hammond, Prescott, Horney and Marbury, JJ.

Pee Curiam.

For the reasons assigned in Judge Cullen’s opinion below, the application for leave to appeal will be denied.

Application denied.
